converted_problem:
Let a = 2400, b = 0.8, c = 1500, d = 0.707, e = 0.9, V = 120, f = 60. Compute:
1) S_total = a / b;
2) Q_total = S_total * sin(acos(b));
3) S_1 = c / d;
4) Q_1 = S_1 * sin(acos(d));
5) Q_2 = Q_total - Q_1;
6) Q_new_total = a * tan(acos(e));
7) Q_C = Q_total - Q_new_total;
8) C = Q_C / (V^2 * 2 * pi * f). Find the value of C in micro units (1 micro = 10^-6).
